@node "1" "File Lister Express (FLE) by Peter Zelezny & Glen Martin"

 .----------------.     _   /|
 |                |     \'o.O'
 |  Introduction  |     =(_._)=
 |                |        U    FLE (c) Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS
 `----------------'

 File Lister Express (FLE) is a total filebase replacement for MAXs BBS
 or MAXs Pro. It allows MAXs to use longer descriptions and file_id's
 and a whole lot of other great features which has made FLE one of the
 best filebase replacements around. Check out the features list!

 The FLE guide has been redone from scratch, and I've made every effort
 to include everything you need to know, etc. I can not guarantee that
 some information may have been omitted or forgotten. If you require
 help or more info, then see the Changes/Info section. Enjoy.

 .------------------.
 | Authors Comments |
 `------------------'

 Peter Zelezny says:

 After seeing DFB (another filebase replacement) I decided i'd write
 my own because I wasn't quiet satisfied with it, so here is the result,
 FLE, the most powerfull filebase replacement for MAXs BBS.

 Glen Martin says:

 I've been running FLE for a long while now, and nothing compares to it.
 It works perfectly on GREMLiNS BBS, and I'll probably stick with it for
 many years to come. I recommend it to every SysOp running MAXs BBS or
 MAXs Pro. It's free and improves the look of your BBS. It's great!

@endnode
@node "2" "File Lister Express (FLE) by Peter Zelezny & Glen Martin"

 .----------------.     _   /|
 |                |     \'o.O'
 |  Requirements  |     =(_._)=
 |                |        U    FLE (c) Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS
 `----------------'

 o MAXs BBS v1.54 or MAXs PRO

 o Kickstart 2.04+

 o Reqtools.library

 o 2 MegaBytes of free HD space (more preferrable!)

 o A lot of free time and dedication... and patience :)

 o Kick-arse Amiga system.

@endnode
@node "3" "File Lister Express (FLE) by Peter Zelezny & Glen Martin"

 .------------.     _   /|
 |            |     \'o.O'
 |  Features  |     =(_._)=
 |            |        U    FLE (c) Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS
 `------------'

 o Extracts file_id.diz from LHA, LZH, LZX, DMS and ZiP archives
   (and you can add your own, eg: ZOO, ARC, ARJ etc).

 o Very Fast file list scroll, doesn't have to search for files in your
   chosen area like some program I know (starts with D, ends with B and
   the middle letter is F).

 o Extraction of file_id.diz is optional in each area.

 o Multiline file descriptions (45 x 12 maximum, or smaller limits).

 o RemoteAccess style tagging system (very quick).

 o New files check for users is optional at every login.

 o External FileBase editor.

 o Three external Checkers (via FileEd):

   FileChecker    - Checks for file existance and fixes file sizes.
   FileDupCheck   - Checks for duplicate files under different names.
   LostFilesCheck - Check for files on HD that aren't in the file list.

 o External User editor (for editing Ratios/Limits, etc).

 o Logoff after downloading feature.

 o Keeps record of top CPS rate for each baud rate, and gives CPS report
   after downloading of files.

 o Truncates annoying long file names when they are uploaded.

 o Notifies users of incomplete uploads.

 o Saves marked files even if user drops carrier.

 o User can tag/mark up to 100 files (not 30 like MAXs!).

 o Option to have file areas in which files are free.

 o Option to add file descriptions to AmigaDOS filenote.

 o Option to have "Creditless" file areas.

 o Kilobyte Ratios (and/or Normal File-Ratios, and/or "Credit" system).

 o Option to execute a command after uploading, this could be to add
   a BBS Advert into the archive or anything you want (optional)!

 o Upload Signatures added to uploaded files.

 o All of the normal list-files options:

   Sorted List      Reverse List     Search String
   Forward List     Newfiles List

 o [V]iew Archive (this option appears while listing files).

 o Option to change the View Archive command lines (you may want to add
   some extra archive types).

 o All colors/text strings and ansi files are editable by the SysOp to
   make the whole system look how you want it.

 o Many other small features.

 o And last, but not least, it looks bloody brilliant. :)

 .-----------------------.
 | Extra Doors/Utilities |
 `-----------------------'

 FLETextList         - Makes a ascii text file of your FLE filelist for
                       users to download in a chosen archive format
                       (txt, lha, zip... etc). The list is updated in 
                       real time (not once a day) and only areas the 
                       user has access to will be included. This door
                       can also create a Amiga Guide list (if the user
                       chooses that option). Run as a MAXs door.

 FLEFileGraph        - Simular to a program called "SectionSummary"
                       but this one is for FLE only and generates a
                       graph of the file sections (to see which section
                       has more files). Run this as a MAXs door.

 FLETicAdder         - Adds inbound tic files to the real file list.
                       Run from shell.

 SignEditor          - This program is for users to edit their upload
                       signature. Run this as a MAXs door.

 FLE_Killdir         - This program will delete unwanted marked file
                       dirs sometimes created in file directories by
                       a possible bug in the Dnload door. Run this
                       from shell, and will display some results.
                       (Written by Olly Koenders)

@endnode
@node "4" "File Lister Express (FLE) by Peter Zelezny & Glen Martin"

 .--------------.     _   /|
 |              |     \'o.O'
 |  Disclaimer  |     =(_._)=
