@node "24" "File Lister Express (FLE) by Peter Zelezny & Glen Martin"

 .----------------.     _   /|
 |                |     \'o.O'
 |  Changes/Info  |     =(_._)=
 |                |        U    FLE (c) Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS
 `----------------'

 This section contains some important changes, and other FLE related info.

 FLE version 0.95 is an update from v0.93. A few things have been fixed,
 deleted, changed and/or raped in some way. It's not a major update and
 there aren't a lot of new features (none actually), just some minor work
 done. I've worked on FLE from time to time, and thought I would release
 a new package, for new and existing FLE SysOps.

 FLE version 0.96 (Final Version) is a VERY-small update for v0.95.


 Important, read on:

 o The password feature has been removed.

 o The MaxMegs and MaxFiles feature never worked, thus has been removed
   completely from the FLE code. The data files "MEGtotal.data" and
   "totals.data" located in "Files:DATAFiLES/" are not really used, but
   must remain as is.

 o If using MAXsPro, the directory "Files:TMP0/" is not needed. When you
   upload, you upload to the true node number directory.

 o Have made changes to the code where extra ansi screens are needed,
   which are included, eg: BeforeUpload.ans is shown before an upload
   sequence. The new ansi's are self explanatory.

 o The Dnload door has a silly bug (which I can't find?) where it will
   create a directory using the user's surname, and in that directory
   it creates a text file of marked files that were downloaded. Fuck'n
   stupid. But my mate Olly wrote the Shell program, FLE_killdir, which
   deletes all these unwated directories. It works, so use it.

 o The User Flags feature wasn't and will not be implemented.

 o With the "Sections.txt" config, if you place a "Y" on the end of the
   Flags (12 characters long), as the 13th character, it will skip a
   file section automatically during the NewFiles door. May be usefull?

 o Any sections you don't want preying eyes on, simply make the axs 10000
   in the "Sections.txt" config, which is skipped during NewFiles, the
   FileGraph and FLETextList, but set up this section in the MAXs menus
   editor, so users can still download, upload, etc from it, with what
   ever axs for normal users.

 o Can you believe this is line 1172 in the CED text editor! ;-)

 o Removed the SysOp_NewFiles and SysOp_MakePublic doors as they are
   hardly used by myself and I think they are useless. If you still want
   to use 'em, then do so from an old FLE package.

 o FLE_Renumber is pretty much useless, but if you want to change a
   section number in the "Section.txt" config (eg: 23) to a section
   number not being used, for reorginising purposes only, and you want
   the FLE filebase also changed to reflect your changes to the config,
   then run this Shell program, and follow the instructions. It will
   change the section number in the filebase data files.

 o The multi-mark option when listing files from the old FLE packages
   was removed as this is a leech option and had a huge crash-BBS bug.
   If you know a BBS still using the leech-mark option, type "1 to 111"
   as if marking files and hit enter.. BOOM! ;) That'll teach 'em for
   not updating FLE to a newer version.

 o The "Exe Upload Area File" (now Exe Upload File), had the option to
   execute a seperate file in each area/section, eg: ??ExeUpload.txt
   where ?? was a section number. This never worked (never knew), so
   it only works for no specified area now, ie: The file is known as
   "UploadExe.txt" and can be executed instead of "MastUploadExe.txt".
   This allows for a different area(s) to have other cmds executed,
   and is set via the flags.

 o Added a local-SysOp sequence when using the FLETextList door.

 o One bug is when a user marks files and is downloading them, then
   aborts the download, any other marked files are lost. I dunno why?

 o Feel free to hack the code and do whatever with the doors/utils.
   And feel free to make extra doors/utils for FLE.

 o Also, refer to the files in the FLEextras directory in the package.


 o I know doubt have missed something, but that's life... Feel free to
   email me with bugs, probs, comments or just for help anytime!

   I'm no gun-expert programmer and ONLY program my own MAXs doors
   from time to time as a hobby, and am not really able to (no time)
   to make "major updates" of FLE. It's provided as is. If anyone out
   there knows HiSoftBasic very well and wants to take over FLE, then
   be my guest (email me). The code was written so "badly" by the
   original author (Peter Zelezny), that it made it impossible for me
   to fix a lot of things with what programming knowledge I have, and
   some external utils I can't even work on and compile 'cause of probs.

   Full source code is available. Email me for it, or check out Aminet.
   If you work on FLE, release anything as FLE, etc. ensure you mention
   the orginal authors of FLE, Peter Zelezny and Glen Martin.

   This version is most likely the FiNAL VERSiON for FLE. [sigh]

   I just use FLE as I love it and it works for me. I provide small
   update packages and support to keep FLE alive, as I believe it's the
   BEST filebase replacment ever (still is) for MAXs BBS and MAXsPro.


 Regards,
   _______ _____ ______ _____ __ __ marty@bit.net.au
